        "id": "D",
        "text": "a² − b² < 0"
      }
    ],
    "correct_option": "A",
    "solution": {
      "final_answer": "a² − b² > a − b",
      "explanation": {
        "concept": "Factorization and comparison of expressions under inequality constraints.",
        "step_by_step": [
          "a² − b² = (a − b)(a + b)",
          "Given a > b > 0 ⇒ (a − b) > 0 and (a + b) > 1",
          "So (a − b)(a + b) > (a − b)",
          "Hence a² − b² > a − b"
        ],
        "why_correct": {
          "A": "Product (a−b)(a+b) exceeds (a−b) since (a+b) > 1."
        },
        "why_incorrect": {
          "B": "Contradicts multiplicative inequality behavior.",
          "C": "Equality only if (a+b)=1, which is not always true.",
          "D": "Expression is positive, not negative."
        }
      }
